parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to stall, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission shifting issues can cause the vehicle to stall or hesitate, making it difficult or impossible to accelerate, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Battery Replacement Disabling Critical Safety Features
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: After replacing the battery, critical safety features such as turn signals, brake lights, and headlights are disabled, increasing the risk of accidents and compromising vehicle safety.
symptoms: Turn signals and brake lights fail to work as needed
front windows cannot be lowered
headlights cannot be controlled (dims and bright lights)
and dash lights are inoperable (speedometer cannot be seen).
